## üîí Security Checks Performed

### Traditional Security
- ‚úÖ IAM permission auditing
- ‚úÖ Encryption validation
- ‚úÖ Network security (VPC endpoints)
- ‚úÖ Audit logging configuration
- ‚úÖ Resource tagging compliance

### GenAI-Specific Security
- ü§ñ Prompt injection vulnerability assessment
- üîç PII detection in model configurations
- üõ°Ô∏è Model access pattern analysis
- üìä Usage anomaly detection setup
- üö® Real-time threat monitoring

## üèóÔ∏è Architecture

The tool is designed with modularity and extensibility in mind:

```
bedrock_security_checker.py
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Security Checks
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Traditional AWS Security
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ GenAI-Specific Security
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Reporting Modes
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Beginner (default)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Expert
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Learning
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Output Formats
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Human-readable text
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ JSON for automation
```

## üîß DevSecOps Integration

### CI/CD Pipeline Example

```yaml
# .github/workflows/bedrock-security.yml
name: Bedrock Security Audit
on: [push, pull_request]

jobs:
  security-check:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - name: Configure AWS credentials
        uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v2
        with:
          aws-access-key-id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}
          aws-secret-access-key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}
          aws-region: us-east-1
      
      - name: Run Bedrock Security Audit
        run: |
          pip install -r requirements.txt
          python bedrock_security_checker.py --output json > security-report.json
          
          # Fail the build if critical issues found
          if [ $? -eq 2 ]; then
            echo "Critical security issues detected!"
            cat security-report.json
            exit 1
          fi
```

## üìà Risk Scoring System

The tool uses a simple 1-10 risk scoring system:

- **9-10**: Critical - Immediate action required
- **7-8**: High - Address within 24 hours
- **4-6**: Medium - Plan remediation
- **1-3**: Low - Best practice improvements

## üõ°Ô∏è GenAI Threat Model Coverage

Based on OWASP Top 10 for LLMs and MITRE ATLAS:

| Threat Category | Coverage | Detection Method |
|----------------|----------|------------------|
| Prompt Injection | ‚úÖ | Pattern matching & guardrail checks |
| Data Poisoning | ‚úÖ | Training source validation |
| Model Theft | ‚úÖ | Access pattern analysis |
| PII Leakage | ‚úÖ | Content scanning |
| Denial of Service | ‚úÖ | Cost & rate monitoring |
| Supply Chain | ‚ö†Ô∏è | Basic model source verification |

